<p>
<s snum=29>Tooling through Sydney on his way to race in the New Zealand Grand Prix, Britain's balding Ace Driver Stirling Moss, 31, all but smothered himself in his own exhaust of self-crimination.</s>
<s snum=30>``I'm a slob'', he announced.</s>
<s snum=31>``My taste is gaudy.</s>
<s snum=32>I'm useless for anything but racing cars.</s>
<s snum=33>I'm ruddy lazy, and I'm getting on in years.</s>
<s snum=34>It gets so frustrating, but then again I don't know what I could do if I gave up racing''.</s>
<s snum=35>Has Moss no stirling virtues?</s>
<s snum=36>``I appreciate beauty''.</s>
